Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounces} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve and peel @yellow onion{1}; thinly slice one half. Mince remaining onion. Remove and discard any large ribs from @kale{4%ounces}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @paprika{1%teaspoon}, and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until lightly browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Creamy Kale ==

While carrots roast, melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add minced onion; cook until lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add kale, @water{1/4%cup}, and @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until kale is wilted and tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat; stir in @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and ¾ of the @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon}. Cover to keep warm.

== Garlic Butter Chicken ==

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounces} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

> Be sure to measure the Tuscan Heat Spice; we sent more.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, about 3-5 minutes per side.

> If chicken begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}.

== Pan Sauce ==

Melt remaining garlic herb butter in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup}. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, creamy kale, and roasted carrots between plates. Spoon pan sauce over chicken and serve.